Full Description: qdPM grew out of a need for a flexible project management tool that would support doing business over  the web.  After evaluating numerous open source solutions and even trying a few for a year or so, we could not find any that had the flexibility we wanted with an easy to use interface. Industries: Non Profit, Property Development, Property Management
Description: NOAHH is on a mission to build houses in partnership with sponsors, volunteers, and families to eliminate poverty housing in New Orleans.
Full Description: NOAHH is a non-profit organization on a mission to build houses in partnership with sponsors, volunteers, and families to eliminate poverty housing in New Orleans. It is an independent affiliate of Habitat for Humanity International (HFHI). The program makes homeownership possible for families who are unable to qualify for traditional home loans but have a stable job, good or no credit, and the willingness to contribute 350 hours of sweat equity to the building of Habitat homes. New Orleans continues to rebuild housing that was destroyed by the devastating flooding of Hurricane Katrina. NOAHH has become a beacon of hope in this rebuilding process by recruiting and deploying tens of thousands of volunteers to construct new homes in damaged, blighted neighborhoods. With the support of our volunteers, donors, and partners across the country and even the world, NOAHH’s homebuilding capacity has increased annually since 2005. It was incorporated in 1983 in New Orleans, Louisiana.

Description: Web-based software solutions
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Blink Logic Inc. develops and markets Web-based software solutions that translate data into tables, charts, and maps. The company's primary software solution, called Blink Logic, presents itself as an information dashboard or front-end solution to the Business Intelligence (BI) and relational database server infrastructure that are used by businesses worldwide. Blink Logic is a zero footprint Web-based solution that allows end-users to create visual dashboard-like live business views on top of their existing relational and OLAP data sources. Blink Logic is deployed on a Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) basis, allowing a customer to pay for its solution on a monthly basis. Blink Logic's data moving feature allows the automatic transfer of customer data across physical infrastructure according to hardware load and performance. Markets The company targets the business intelligence software market and the business data market with the same technology and solutions. Business Intelligence Software Market: This market includes various tools and applications focused on helping knowledge workers and business managers to access and analyze business data and performance metrics. Business Data Market: This market includes companies that are in the business of selling industry and market research data. Competition The company's major competitors include Cognos, Business Objects, Microsoft, Oracle, Microstrategy, and SAS. Its competitors also include Panorama Software, Dundas Software, Corda Technologies, LucidEra, Pivotlink, iDashboards, and Targit.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Internet Services, Software

Description: J. Patton Sports Marketing provides brand protection and brand management solutions to manage, enhance, and authenticate brands.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: JPatton is provider of brand protection solutions, in patented holographic security technologies and digital asset management. The company establish  in 1996 by Jim Patton, a 20-year marketing veteran of the soft drink industry. In 1998, JPatton created a digital solution for The Collegiate Licensing Company to eliminate the need for physical artwork distribution to its clients’ licensees. As the company added new brand protection services and clients, JPatton expanded from 3 to 12 employees and moved to a new location in Norcross, Georgia. Eleven years ago, JPatton developed its holographic security technology. In 2005, JPatton’s current managing director, Pete Reyes engineered the state-of-the-art equipment, customized specifically for patented holographic technologies. Today, all production takes place in JPatton’s 33,000 square foot manufacturing facility in Duluth, Georgia. Their hologram technology has protected more than two billion products worldwide and been distributed to over 3,200 manufacturing facilities throughout five continents for application. They offer a variety of holographic products, including laminates, hangtags, labels, stickers, laminate films, security holograms, holographic tapes and tamper resistant holograms. JPatton works with domestic and international partners in various industries including Brand Licensing, Sports Marketing, Software, Government Agencies, Manufacturing and Not-For-Profit Organizations.
